      name: "Combined Oral Contraceptive (ethinyl estradiol/norgestimate)",
      type: "Hormonal contraceptive (estrogen-progestin combination)",
      action: "Suppresses ovulation via inhibition of GnRH pulsatility, LH surge, and FSH; thickens cervical mucus and thins endometrium to prevent implantation",
      sideEffects: "Nausea, breast tenderness, breakthrough bleeding, headache; increased risk of VTE, stroke, and MI in high-risk patients",
