    pearls: ["PCOS is diagnosed using Rotterdam criteria (2 of 3: oligo/anovulation, hyperandrogenism, polycystic ovaries) after excluding other causes such as thyroid disease, hyperprolactinemia, and congenital adrenal hyperplasia","Chronic anovulation in PCOS leads to unopposed estrogen exposure, increasing endometrial hyperplasia and cancer risk -- progestin withdrawal or continuous progestin is essential for endometrial protection","Endometriosis definitive diagnosis requires laparoscopic visualization and biopsy, but empiric treatment based on clinical presentation is appropriate and recommended before surgical intervention","GnRH agonist treatment is limited to 6 months without add-back therapy due to significant bone density loss (up to 6% over 6 months); add-back therapy allows extended use","The PALM-COEIN classification system for AUB provides a structured approach: structural causes (Polyp, Adenomyosis, Leiomyoma, Malignancy) require imaging and possible biopsy; non-structural causes (Coagulopathy, Ovulatory dysfunction, Endometrial, Iatrogenic) require laboratory evaluation","Ovarian torsion is a gynecological emergency -- suspect in any patient with sudden severe unilateral pelvic pain and an adnexal mass; requires emergent surgical intervention within 6 hours to preserve ovarian function"],
